{"version": "https://jsonfeed.org/version/1.1", "title": "Confluent", "home_page_url": "https://xcat2.github.io/confluent-docs/", "feed_url": "https://xcat2.github.io/confluent-docs/feed_json_updated.json", "description": "Confluent documentation", "icon": null, "authors": [{"name": "Confluent Community"}], "language": "en", "items": [{"id": "https://xcat2.github.io/confluent-docs/release_notes/2017/12/04/recent-confluent-features/", "url": "https://xcat2.github.io/confluent-docs/release_notes/2017/12/04/recent-confluent-features/", "title": "Recent Confluent Features", "content_html": "<h1>Recent Confluent Features</h1>\n<p>Confluent has a new discovery mechanism.  This allows for zero-power xCAT style discovery and configuration of lenovo systems.</p>", "image": "https://xcat2.github.io/confluent-docs/assets/images/social/release_notes/2017/12/04/recent-confluent-features.png", "date_modified": "2026-07-02T18:50:20+00:00", "date_published": "2017-12-04T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": null}, {"id": "https://xcat2.github.io/confluent-docs/release_notes/2018/11/14/210-confluent-release/", "url": "https://xcat2.github.io/confluent-docs/release_notes/2018/11/14/210-confluent-release/", "title": "2.1.0 Confluent release", "content_html": "<h1>2.1.0 Confluent release</h1>\n<p>There is an update to the HPC software stack, bringing xCAT to 2.14.3.lenovo3, based on 2.14.3,\nand confluent is brought to 2.1.0.</p>", "image": "https://xcat2.github.io/confluent-docs/assets/images/social/release_notes/2018/11/14/210-confluent-release.png", "date_modified": "2026-07-02T18:50:20+00:00", "date_published": "2018-11-14T00:00:00+00:00", "authors": [], "tags": null}, {"id": "https://xcat2.github.io/confluent-docs/release_notes/2019/04/17/220-confluent-release/", "url": "https://xcat2.github.io/confluent-docs/release_notes/2019/04/17/220-confluent-release/", "title": "2.2.0 Confluent release", "content_html": "<h1>2.2.0 Confluent release</h1>\n<p>There is an update to the HPC so